    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>
      The corresponding augmented matrix can be put in REF:
      <me>\begin{bmatrix} 1 \amp 2 \amp 8 \\ 3 \amp 1 \amp 3 \\ 0 \amp 5 \amp 17 \end{bmatrix} \sim \begin{bmatrix} 1 \amp 2 \amp 8 \\ 0 \amp -5 \amp -21 \\ 0 \amp 5 \amp 17 \end{bmatrix} \sim \begin{bmatrix} 1 \amp 2 \amp 8 \\ 0 \amp -5 \amp -21 \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp -4 \end{bmatrix}
      </me>
      Is <m>{\mathbf{b}}</m> in the plane spanned by the columns of <m>A</m>?
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>
  </p>
</li>

